1
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:16,840
-(ZYGON GROWLING)
-(SHUDDERING)

2
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:18,240
The Doctor will save me.
The Doctor will save me.

3
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:19,320
The Doctor will save me.

4
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:22,720
Excuse me, I'm going
to need my inhaler.

5
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:27,600
Any second now you are
going to stop that countdown.

6
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:28,720
-Both of you. Together.
-(TIMER BEEPING)

7
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:31,560
And then you are going to negotiate
the most perfect treaty of all time.

8
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:33,080
Safeguards all round,
completely fair on both sides.

9
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:34,400
And the key to
perfect negotiation.

10
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:35,560
Not knowing
what side you're on.

11
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:39,760
So, for the next few hours,

12
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,320
until we decide
to let you out.

13
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:43,080
No one in this room
will be able to remember

14
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:44,880
if they are human or Zygon.

15
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,600
Whoopsy daisy!

16
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:48,520
(DEVICES WHIRRING)

17
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,840
(TIMER BEEPING)

18
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:59,720
Cancel the detonation!

19
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:06,000
-Hello.
-Hello.

20
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:08,000
-Do you want to...
-No, you can if you...

21
00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:09,680
BOTH: Should
we do it together?

22
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,760
Operation Double.

23
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,800
The Zygon peace treaty.

24
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:16,560
-I'm Osgood.
-I'm also Osgood.

25
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:18,360
Remember that,
it'll be important later.

26
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,480
Operation Double
is a covert operation,

27
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:22,080
outside of
normal UNIT strictures,

28
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:26,640
to resettle and rehouse an alien race,
in secrecy, on planet Earth.

29
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:30,520
With UNIT's help, 20 million Zygons have
been allowed to take human form,

30
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,720
been dispersed
around the world

31
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,720
and are now living amongst us.

32
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,600
We're making this
in case something goes wrong.

33
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:37,400
In case UNIT is infiltrated.

34
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:40,840
In case something occurs
to unmask the Zygons.

35
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:43,080
Or in case one
or both of us dies.

36
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,400
(SOBBING)

37
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,600
The Zygons a peaceful race.

38
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:58,320
Their shape-changing abilities should
not be considered a weapon.

39
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,880
It's a survival mechanism.

40
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,800
They embed themselves
in other cultures,

41
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,400
and live out their lives
in their new bodies

42
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,360
in peace and harmony.

43
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:06,600
Mainly.

44
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:09,600
Any race is capable of
the best and the worst.

45
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,960
Every race is peaceful and warlike.

46
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,160
Good and evil.

47
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,760
My race is no exception.

48
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,880
And neither is mine.

49
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:18,000
If one Zygon goes rogue.

50
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,800
Or one human.

51
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,800
Then the ceasefire will break.

52
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,560
That's why the Doctor left us this.

53
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,280
He called it the Osgood box.

54
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,440
If you've been paying attention,

55
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,520
you'll be able to guess why.

56
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,800
This is the last resort.

57
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,280
The final sanction.

58
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,040
Pray this box is never needed.

59
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:38,760
Because if it is, that means
the ceasefire is breaking.

60
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:41,000
And with 20 million
shape-changing Zygons

61
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,400
dispersed around the world...

62
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:45,120
That is the nightmare scenario.

63
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:47,920
-(GUNFIRE)
-(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

64
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,760
-(GLASS SHATTERING)
- (SHRIEKS)

65
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,320
(INHALING)

66
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,200
(DOOR OPENING)

67
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,280
(GROWLING)

68
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,240
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

69
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,280
(MOBILE CHIMES)

70
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,920
-(ZYGON GROWLING)
- (SHRIEKS)

71
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,880
(SCREAMING)

72
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,960
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

73
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:04,720
(GUITAR PLAYING AMAZING GRACE)

74
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,520
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

75
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:05,480
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

76
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,280
Come on, kids, no pushing.

77
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:21,320
Hi, this is Clara Oswald. I am probably
on the tube or in outer space.

78
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,600
-Leave a message.
-(LINE BEEPS)

79
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,040
Hello, it's Doctor Disco.

80
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,640
I'm in the 21st century.

81
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:29,360
I don't know what month.

82
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:32,200
I'm staking out some of the most
dangerous creatures imaginable.

83
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,600
Operating under deep cover.

84
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,480
Trying not to attract suspicion.

85
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,960
Give me a call, Clara.

86
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:41,640
Nightmare scenario.
I'm worried.

87
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:44,600
Okay. Hey, monster, hi.
Cinderella.

88
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,400
Down, off monkey bars.

89
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,960
Listen to me, we've got to talk.

90
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,520
Get me Colonel Walsh.

91
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,680
And I need you to coordinate

92
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,480
the Operation Double Locations.

93
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,760
There are 20 million Zygons.

94
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,840
And most of the data was with...

95
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,360
Her.

96
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,600
KATE: Do what you can.

97
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:12,360
Start with any that have intelligence
flags from the past six months.

98
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:17,040
-(COMPUTER BEEPING)
-Walsh coming through.

99
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,280
WALSH: (ON COMPUTER)
Walsh, Turmezistan.

100
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,480
Any new arrivals?

101
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,560
One. Pictures aren't very good.

102
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,760
Can you zoom in on the prisoner?

103
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,880
It's her. Get into her files,

104
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:34,320
we have to assume they
have been compromised.

105
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,760
JAC: Um, too late.

106
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,920
The encryption system
has already been hacked.

107
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,880
And they've sent through
another video.

108
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:47,680
Look, I admire you, okay?
I think you're ingenious.

109
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,520
Pretending to be a couple
of seven year olds.

110
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,800
It's a splendid way to
conceal your blobbyness.

111
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:55,760
But let's not pretend,
you are very blobby.

112
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,960
In fact, you two are the big blobs,

113
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,600
and you are not to withdraw
the ceasefire.

114
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,440
Fine, fine. Bury your heads.

115
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,080
Listen to me. Listen.

116
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,360
There are other factions.

117
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,920
I know there are
other blobby factions

118
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,000
that you don't control.

119
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,000
They're planning something.

120
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:19,160
And if we don't get
together and stop it,

121
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:21,680
it will be the end of this.
Of all of you.

122
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,880
This is our jurisdiction, Doctor.

123
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,520
These are our creatures.

124
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,120
We are close to finding them.

125
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,720
They are our children
and we will deal with them.

126
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,480
You kids are out of control.

127
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,080
-I'm taking this out of your hands.
-(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

128
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:36,080
Don't even think about
going anywhere.

129
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,480
Are you phoning me
with your backside again

130
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,240
or are you really sending me
a distress signal?

131
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,560
KATE: I'm really
sending you a distress signal.

132
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,840
They've kidnapped Osgood

133
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:49,560
and they've stolen the
location of every Zygon on Earth.

134
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,360
Doctor, the ceasefire
has broken down.

135
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,920
(GAS HISSING)

136
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,240
Hey! Away! Away!

137
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,360
Got a situation!

138
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,560
Out of the way!
Out of the way! Out of the way!

139
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,560
Move! Move away!

140
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,240
(GIRL SCREAMING)

141
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,920
(TYRES SQUEALING)

142
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:26,240
"UNIT troops will be destroyed

143
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,880
"wherever they are in the world.

144
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:31,720
"The enemies of our race
will be destroyed

145
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,720
"wherever they are in the world.

146
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,200
"The war is about to begin.

147
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,480
"There will be truth.

148
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,920
"Or there will be
consequences."”

149
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,080
-(LINE RINGING)
-Hi this is Clara Oswald.

150
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:00,600
I'm probably on the tube
or in outer space.

151
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:02,520
-Leave a message.
-(LINE BEEPS)

152
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,640
Call me now.

153
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,440
(MOBILE PHONE CHIMES)

154
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,280
(CHUCKLES)

155
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,960
(LINE RINGING)

156
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,320
-(LINE BEEPS)
-DOCTOR: Hello, it's Doctor Disco.

157
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,440
-Hello.
-Oh, hello.

158
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,000
Sandeep, hello.

159
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,440
You okay?

160
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:36,400
I can't find my
mummy and daddy.

161
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,000
Well, why don't you wait here

162
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,760
and I can go see
if I can find them.

163
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,640
Hello?

164
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,600
Hello?

165
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:14,440
(GASPS) Oh, sorry. Um...

166
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:18,640
Your little boy is out there.
He couldn't find you.

167
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:24,600
MAN: Daddy's here.

168
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,960
We can take him.

169
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:31,240
(SANDEEP SCREAMING)

170
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,040
Is he... Is he okay?

171
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,400
Everything's fine.

172
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,080
(LINE RINGING)

173
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:59,320
Did you just call yourself
"Doctor Disco"?

174
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:13,440
KATE: This is where the Zygon
High Command had their secret base.

175
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:14,520
CLARA: A junior school?

176
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,600
KATE: Terms of the settlement,
Operation Double, were these.

177
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:20,320
Twenty million Zygons,
the entire hatchery,

178
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,360
were allowed to be born
and to stay on Earth.

179
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,240
They were permitted
to permanently take up

180
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:26,160
the form of the nearest
available human beings.

181
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,240
In this case,

182
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,720
a large percentage of
the population of the UK.

183
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,080
KATE: He left us with an
impossible situation, Doctor.

184
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,320
Yes, I know. It's called "peace”.

185
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:41,600
What about the two little
girl commanders?

186
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:42,880
Weren't they helping him?

187
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,480
KATE: Well, they've been
almost impossible to deal with

188
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,560
since Osgood left.

189
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:48,840
Secretive, uncommunicative.
We've known there's something going on.

190
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,480
Some radicalisation.

191
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:53,640
Some revolution in
the younger brood.

192
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,760
They said they had it under control.

193
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,520
The Zygon Command Centre.

194
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,840
That's the control polyp
for all Zygons on Earth.

195
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,080
JAC: It's horrible.

196
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,560
Could you...
Would you mind? Thank you.

197
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,960
If this has been compromised...

198
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,440
Zygons are wide open.

199
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,160
They'll be starting to panic,

200
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:36,400
starting to worry.

201
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,280
Doctor, do you want to
be alone with that thing?

202
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,680
It's a command computer.

203
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:47,080
You operate it by
titivating the fronds.

204
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,120
Are you enjoying that?

205
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,840
I snogged a Zygon once.
Old habits...

206
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,480
(POLYP GROANS)

207
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:57,320
Still got the old magic.

208
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,880
So Osgood's
been kidnapped, right?

209
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,080
I though Osgood was dead.

210
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,000
There have always been two of her
ever since the ceasefire.

211
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,320
We never knew
which one was real.

212
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,720
-Both of them.
-Okay. Which one was Zygon?

213
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,880
Both of them. They would
have maintained a live link.

214
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:12,040
They were both Zygon and human
at the same time.

215
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,280
They not only
administered the peace,

216
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,040
they were the peace.

217
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,600
When the other Osgood died,

218
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:19,440
the survivor went
pretty much mad with grief.

219
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:22,080
Then she just disappeared.
Went undercover in the States.

220
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:24,960
Now, of course,
the rebels have her.

221
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,200
(SQUELCHING)

222
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:29,040
Ah. Okay.

223
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:32,560
Zygons hatched and
dispersed all over,

224
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,120
but something's gone wrong.

225
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:37,640
Mexico border, North Asia,

226
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:40,600
West Africa, Australia.

227
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,840
Panic, paranoia.

228
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,480
What would happen
if they knew who we were?

229
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:46,560
(TABLET CHIMES)

230
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:49,120
We've received another video.

231
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:56,320
That's the Zygon High Command.
It's Jemima and Claudette.

232
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:59,560
ZYGON: We have been betrayed.

233
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:02,440
We were sold.

234
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:05,960
Our rights were violated.

235
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:10,640
We demand the right
to be ourselves.

236
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,600
No more lies.

237
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:16,600
No more lies!

238
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:19,880
(GROWLING)

239
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:35,240
We are now
the Zygon High Command.

240
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:38,200
All traitors will die.

241
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:41,440
"Truth or consequences”.

242
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:50,960
DOCTOR: So, we have a Zygon
revolution on our hands.

243
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,680
We need to open negotiations.

244
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:53,880
I am not negotiating with them.

245
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,680
As far as they are concerned
everyone's a traitor.

246
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:57,680
If you're not gonna negotiate,
what are you gonna do?

247
00:14:57,760 --> 00:15:00,680
They're holed up in this
settlement in Turmezistan.

248
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,960
It's where they've taken Osgood.

249
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:04,040
I'm going to order
Colonel Walsh to bomb it.

250
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,520
Isn't there a solution that
doesn't involve bombing everyone?

251
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:09,600
The treaty has been
comprehensively violated, Doctor.

252
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:11,080
This is a splinter group.

253
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,000
The rest of the Zygons,
the vast majority,

254
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,560
they want to live in peace.

255
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:17,640
You start bombing them
you'll radicalise the lot.

256
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:20,960
It's exactly what
the splinter group wants.

257
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,680
"Truth or Consequences".

258
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,240
What exactly does that mean?

259
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,560
It's just the usual
kind of nonsense

260
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:26,800
these idiots call themselves.

261
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:28,960
-It's in New Mexico.
-KATE: What?

262
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:32,440
It's a town in New Mexico,
Truth or Consequences.

263
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,960
Um, they renamed
it after a TV show

264
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:36,080
for a bet or something.

265
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,520
It's a Trivial Pursuit question.

266
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,080
I used to memorise
Trivial Pursuit questions

267
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:41,280
so I could win.

268
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,200
That's the last place
we received signal

269
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,040
from Osgood's phone, isn't it?

270
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,240
New Mexico.

271
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,400
Okay, Kate Stewart,
no bombs for you.

272
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:52,000
Go to Truth or Consequences.
See what you can find out.

273
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,040
The Doctor will go
to Turmezistan,

274
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:57,280
negotiate peace,
rescue Osgood, prevent this war.

275
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,640
'Cause that's what he does.

276
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:01,040
Clara, Jac, you stay here.

277
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,720
This is your country.

278
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,480
Protect it from
the scary monsters,

279
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:05,760
and also from the Zygons.

280
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,240
Bye.

281
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:10,360
Oh. Um, do you still have
the presidential aircraft?

282
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,480
I thought you didn't like
being president of the world.

283
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,920
No. But I like poncing
about in the big plane.

284
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,800
How many troops do you have?

285
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,720
(SCOFFS) Not many.

286
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:31,640
Usually, on bigger cases,
we can draft in from the regular army,

287
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,200
we can't do that now.

288
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:35,520
Secrecy of the project
has to be maintained.

289
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:38,000
Have you got any
snazzy weapons?

290
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,960
There was an attempted
Zygon invasion before,

291
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,360
in the '70s, '80s,

292
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,360
one of our staff
was a naval surgeon,

293
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:47,080
who worked at Porton Down
when they captured Zygons,

294
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:49,440
developed Z-67.

295
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,600
It's a nerve gas.

296
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:52,000
Unravels their DNA.

297
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,240
Basically, turns them inside out.

298
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,720
-Where do you keep it?
-(CHUCKLES)

299
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,720
We don't. It was taken.

300
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,600
The formula. The lot.

301
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:01,680
Who took it?

302
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:03,360
Somebody with a Tardis.

303
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,080
They are ready for you, ma'am.

304
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,640
Keep in touch.

305
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,480
Oh! I just need to swing by home

306
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:12,920
and grab a couple of things.

307
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,360
Yeah, of course.

308
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,640
MAN: Quick.
Before someone sees us.

309
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:34,840
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

310
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,360
(SANDEEP SCREAMING)

311
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,640
It's really slow, we can catch them.

312
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,120
Come on.

313
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:05,400
-CLARA: It's slower than usual.
-JAC: What's wrong with it?

314
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,960
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

315
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,880
Is there a cellar or somewhere
else they could have gone?

316
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,440
No.

317
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:24,120
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

318
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,880
Ugh. What is that?

319
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:51,080
No, don't.

320
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,280
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

321
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:35,360
(SANDEEP SCREAMING)

322
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:42,360
MAN: All together.
Put them all together.

323
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:52,000
I think we need to get
some reinforcements.

324
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:55,160
MAN: Over there.
Put them there.

325
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:24,320
Approaching target at 1006512.

326
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,880
-Confirm strike order.
-Order confirmed.

327
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,040
At ease.

328
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:33,120
I'm the president of the world.

329
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,240
I'm here to rescue people,

330
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:37,280
and generally establish
happiness all over the place.

331
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:39,320
The Doctor.
Doctor Funkenstein.

332
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,040
Yes, we know who you are.

333
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,600
LISA: Going to strike altitude.

334
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:44,840
What's going on here?

335
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:47,760
Fun and games?

336
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:49,920
WOMAN: (ON RADIO)
74. Negative.

337
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,200
MAN: (ON RADIO)
We're 700 metres lower.

338
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:53,400
700 metres lower
than planned. Over.

339
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,640
You're not bombing that town.

340
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:56,840
That's where they're
holding my friend.

341
00:20:56,920 --> 00:21:00,520
They're dangerous, and your friend
is almost certainly dead.

342
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,040
I'm not gonna
allow them to disperse.

343
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,880
You can't track a shapeshifter.

344
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:05,440
Visual on the target.

345
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,440
WALSH: Confirm strike.

346
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:10,680
Colonel.

347
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,000
WALSH: Confirm strike.

348
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:21,760
Confirm strike.

349
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:24,520
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

350
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:32,080
Confirm strike.
Confirm strike.

351
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:34,560
Strike aborted.
Strike aborted.

352
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,960
Well, that's interesting.

353
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:00,840
(DOG BARKING)

354
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:31,880
(ZYGON GROWLING)

355
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,480
(FLIES BUZZING)

356
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,080
Hello?

357
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:45,120
Hello?

358
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,240
You one of them?

359
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,600
I'm a friend. I've come to help.

360
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,720
Alone?

361
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,160
Have you come to help alone?

362
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,360
What happened here?

363
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,240
You must have brought back-up.

364
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:34,400
Where's your back-up?

365
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:36,760
-Tell me!
-First, tell me why I need it.

366
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:43,160
We think it's
a Zygon training camp.

367
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,000
We never see more than one or two of
them outside at any one time,

368
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:47,400
but they always take
different shapes.

369
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:49,640
We don't know
how many there really are.

370
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,280
We don't know how
they come and go.

371
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,840
Whether they go
through tunnels,

372
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:55,640
or whether they turn into dogs
and run out across the hills.

373
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:58,160
So that's what we'll find out.

374
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:00,040
We should have that gas.

375
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:02,400
We should be able
to rip them inside out.

376
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:05,200
Colonel, take it easy.
They are trying to unsettle you.

377
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,400
They are trying to
make you paranoid, panicked.

378
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,480
Any living thing in this world,

379
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:10,880
including my family and friends,

380
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:14,120
could turn into a Zygon
and kill me any second now.

381
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:17,080
It's not paranoia when it's real.

382
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:29,800
I've been looking into this.

383
00:25:29,880 --> 00:25:31,800
There have been reports
all over London

384
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:33,840
of strange activity in lifts.

385
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:36,640
I've patched into CCTV
from Scotland Yard,

386
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,240
all the elevators I could find.

387
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:40,960
Now, this is SOAS.

388
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:42,960
People dragging bundles.

389
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,600
They go down, down,
down, down, down,

390
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:46,160
a few minutes go by and then...

391
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:49,200
They're all gone.

392
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:53,000
There is something very wrong
happening underneath London.

393
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:01,840
The Brits came two years ago.

394
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:04,120
We didn't want them.
They just... (SIGHS)

395
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,480
They just turned up.

396
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:09,120
No jobs, nowhere to live, no money.

397
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,680
And they were...

398
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,840
They were odd.

399
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,280
(SIGHS) They started
getting into fights.

400
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,360
-A couple of them got killed.
-More than a couple.

401
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,480
What happened here?

402
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:23,480
Well, after the murders
they started banding together.

403
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:28,880
And then, one day,
one of them changed.

404
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:30,200
"Changed"?

405
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,360
One of them was
walking down West Main,

406
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:33,960
and suddenly...

407
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,880
It turned into a...

408
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:39,720
(EXHALES) A reptile.

409
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,960
They just came for us.

410
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:48,000
They turned into monsters
and they came for us.

411
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,680
And (STUTTERS)
we couldn't fight them.

412
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:52,360
You can't tell who's who.

413
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:55,360
(SIGHS) They can turn
your own family against you.

414
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:59,560
Have you seen her?

415
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:00,680
Yeah, she was here.

416
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:04,280
She was at the motel
asking questions. Before.

417
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:07,280
(SIGHS) Everybody's gone.

418
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:09,240
Where?

419
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:10,640
(SIGHS)

420
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:16,880
WALSH: (ON RADIO)
Okay, listen carefully.

421
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:22,200
Once we get to the village we have a
30-minute window before the air strike.

422
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:40,200
We all know what
a rabbit warren this place is,

423
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:43,000
but we've got intel they're
holed up inside the church.

424
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:45,520
Hitchley, you take the front,
Stormit, draw their fire,

425
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,640
the Doctor and I
will take the back.

426
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:50,160
This is our object.

427
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:53,600
We need to get her back safely.

428
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,560
Try to kill as few of
them as possible.

429
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:58,080
I need to have someone
to negotiate with.

430
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,240
You know what
they're capable of.

431
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:02,440
Do not fall victim to it.

432
00:28:04,360 --> 00:28:06,240
Trap open. Code green.

433
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:08,200
HITCHLEY: Let's move out.

434
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:48,920
Come out.
Throw down your weapons.

435
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:52,280
Come out!
We have you surrounded.

436
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:55,160
Come out of there!

437
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:04,240
Come out!
We have you surrounded.

438
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:10,320
I don't have any weapons.
Please.

439
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:13,840
-Take aim. On my command.
-(GUNS COCKING)

440
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:17,360
No. No, don't. Please.

441
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:21,840
Johnny, you don't understand.

442
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,800
You're not my mother.
Don't use my name.

443
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:26,840
They took us here.

444
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,800
They came to the
house and took us.

445
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:31,960
They took your sister, me.

446
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:33,840
You stay where you are.

447
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:37,760
It's not us who are the imposters.

448
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:40,120
Don't let them trick you.

449
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:43,760
It's your commanders.
Your chief.

450
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:45,960
They're the aliens.

451
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:47,320
WALSH: (ON RADIO)
Do not fall victim.

452
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:48,720
Ask for details.

453
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:52,440
She is a copy. Ask her something
only your mum could know.

454
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:54,280
Mom, I'm gonna have to
ask you some questions.

455
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:59,000
Don't do this. You know it's me.

456
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:00,560
Don't let them trick you.

457
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,480
Date and place of my birth.

458
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:06,880
They brought us here.
They're using us against you.

459
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,200
I'm scared.

460
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:12,720
Please. I'm so scared.

461
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:14,280
Name of my favourite teddy bear.

462
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:16,960
I don't remember.

463
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:19,960
I'm sorry, I don't.

464
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:23,000
(ON RADIO) Don't kill me
because I can't remember.

465
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:24,600
Hitchley.

466
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:39,280
Stay back. All of you,
stay back from them!

467
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:42,040
That is not your mother.
It's an alien hostile.

468
00:30:42,120 --> 00:30:45,480
WOMAN: We're not those
creatures, we're hostages.

469
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:46,600
Kill it!

470
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:49,320
I can prove it.
I can prove who we are.

471
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:51,840
Just come inside, I'll show you.

472
00:30:51,920 --> 00:30:53,000
Don't go in there.

473
00:30:53,080 --> 00:30:55,840
-Please.
-You are not my mom.

474
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:59,440
Oh, God.

475
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,000
You're going to kill me.

476
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:03,600
-Mom, please.
-WOMAN: You are.

477
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:07,120
You're going to kill me.

478
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:10,600
I love you.

479
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:14,240
I forgive you and I love you.

480
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:15,800
(SOBBING)

481
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:16,960
Do it!

482
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:27,280
What proof?

483
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:29,520
Don't go in there.
You're going to your death.

484
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,800
(ON RADIO) Hitchley, kill it.

485
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,320
HITCHLEY: Let's go.

486
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,880
Over and out, ma'am.

487
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:37,560
Oh, damn it!

488
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,040
Damn it!

489
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:44,240
This is poisonous.
Just let me go in and talk.

490
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:51,000
(GUNSHOTS)

491
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:03,600
WALSH: They've executed my men.

492
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:05,360
DOCTOR: Where are the Zygons?

493
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:08,280
We need to bomb
the hell out of this place,

494
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:09,800
it's infested with these things.

495
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:12,520
We can't tell who
the enemy is any more.

496
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,440
We can't count them,
and we can't track them.

497
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:17,120
I'm not gonna let you do that.

498
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,480
I just lost my men.

499
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:20,520
I'll quite happily bomb
the hell out of anywhere.

500
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:23,080
We need to move.
Strike's on its way.

501
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:24,640
I need to find Osgood.

502
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:27,240
You've got 10 minutes.

503
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,120
-OSGOOD: Help! Help!
-DOCTOR: Osgood?

504
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:41,680
-Osgood?
-Doctor.

505
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:43,600
-Osgood?
-Doctor, I'm here.

506
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:45,200
Osgood!

507
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:47,760
Help! Doctor, I'm down here.

508
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:51,200
-Osgood!
-Doctor.

509
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,400
Doctor!

510
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:06,840
-Doctor.
-Osgood.

511
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,080
(PLANES PASSING)

512
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:13,600
Got to get you out.
They're gonna bomb this place.

513
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:16,000
-What do the Zygons want?
-They're training,

514
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:19,200
practising new skills.
Doctor, what are you doing here?

515
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:20,800
-(DEVICE WHIRRING)
-Rescuing you.

516
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,640
In quite a dashing way,
I might add.

517
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,120
They fled through the tunnels.

518
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,400
They're going back to the UK.

519
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:27,520
If you're here, they've
got you out of the way.

520
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:29,560
-Who's left in the UK?
-Clara.

521
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:31,400
ZYGON: (SCREECHING) Clara!

522
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:34,280
DOCTOR: Oh, hello.

523
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:36,680
(EXPLOSION)

524
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:44,480
They've started.
So much for "10 minutes”.

525
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,640
(EXPLOSION)

526
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:53,280
KATE: You've found something?
What do you want me to see?

527
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:56,000
(FLIES BUZZING)

528
00:33:57,720 --> 00:34:00,560
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
-Oh, God.

529
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:04,600
Were those all people?

530
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:12,720
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING
IN DISTANCE)

531
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:27,040
JAC: Oh, it's an odd
world nowadays, isn't it?

532
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:29,920
It's always been an odd world.

533
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:33,640
Mmm-hmm. I mean,
doesn't it feel sometimes

534
00:34:33,720 --> 00:34:35,680
that things are
coming to an end,

535
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:38,760
everything is just going nuts?

536
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:41,520
You're middle-aged,
that's what it is. No offence.

537
00:34:42,680 --> 00:34:46,120
Everybody middle-aged always thinks
the world is about to come to an end.

538
00:34:46,200 --> 00:34:48,600
(CHUCKLES) Never does.

539
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:55,240
It's here.

540
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,800
Oh, my God.

541
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:13,040
(ON MOBILE PHONE)
Hi, this is Clara Oswald.

542
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,800
I'm probably on the tube
or in outer space.

543
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,200
-Leave a message.
-(LINE BEEPS)

544
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,800
Can you change your
voicemail message, please?

545
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,520
It's getting very boring.

546
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:25,320
Oh, I see you've accessorised it.

547
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:26,920
Yes.

548
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,560
The old question marks.

549
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:30,280
You used to wear question marks.

550
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:32,640
Oh, I know. Yes, I did.

551
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:35,520
They were nice. Why don't
you wear them any more?

552
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,040
Oh, I do.

553
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:40,760
I've got
question mark underpants.

554
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:42,760
Makes one wonder
what the question is.

555
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:52,080
Which one are you,

556
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,680
human or Zygon?

557
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:58,160
-I don't answer that question.
-Why not?

558
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:00,280
Because there isn't
a question to answer.

559
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:02,040
I don't accept it.

560
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:05,920
My sister and I were the living
embodiment of the peace we made.

561
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:08,160
I will give all the lives
that I have to protect it.

562
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:10,720
You want to know
who I am, Doctor?

563
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:14,920
I am the peace.
I am human and Zygon.

564
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:20,160
Like a hybrid.

565
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,000
A hybrid, if you like.

566
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:27,680
Well, I am proud to
know you, Osgood.

567
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:30,200
And I promise that
I won't tell anyone

568
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:31,360
that you're a human.

569
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:35,760
Zygons need to keep
the human original alive

570
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,720
to refresh the body print.

571
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:40,120
If you were a Zygon,
you would have changed back

572
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:42,080
within days of your sister's death.

573
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,920
Those were the old rules.

574
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:45,880
Before, Zygons could pluck
loved ones from your memory

575
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,320
and wear their faces.

576
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:50,640
Zygons only need to
keep the original alive

577
00:36:50,720 --> 00:36:52,800
if they need more
information from them.

578
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:57,680
If the interrogation is over,
then the original can die.

579
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:11,160
Oh, my God.

580
00:37:15,240 --> 00:37:17,320
These are Zygon pods.

581
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:23,280
I think you might be right.

582
00:37:23,720 --> 00:37:25,040
About what?

583
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:28,880
The end of the world.

584
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:42,200
(SNARLING)

585
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:48,920
Bit of first things firstness.

586
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:51,000
What's your name?

587
00:37:56,560 --> 00:37:58,760
My name is... Well...

588
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:01,000
Well, you can call me the Doctor.

589
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:04,080
But then you knew that, didn't you?

590
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:07,840
You want something.
What is it?

591
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:11,440
You are the president of the world.

592
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:12,680
I suppose so.

593
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:17,280
We want the world. (LAUGHING)

594
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:39,440
Okay. It looks like whole buildings

595
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,640
full of people have been pinched.

596
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:42,760
In fact, it looks like a whole

597
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:44,320
London full of people
have been pinched.

598
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:46,800
But, we've got here early,
and they're still growing.

599
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:49,440
We have to neutralise these
before they hatch.

600
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:51,400
Take your positions.

601
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:55,600
Do you know what?

602
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,760
I'm enjoying this.

603
00:38:58,200 --> 00:38:59,440
-Clara.
-What?

604
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:01,320
We don't know
that's what these are.

605
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:04,440
Oh, come on. These are
eggs or pods or whatever.

606
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:05,520
Look.

607
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:15,320
Oh, my God, that's me.

608
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,680
I think we should wait.

609
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:22,240
Look, they're here.

610
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,840
They're growing duplicates of us.

611
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:28,440
We have to destroy them.
I've seen this happen before.

612
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:30,640
It happened to that little boy,

613
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:32,360
they took his parents
and then they took him.

614
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:34,840
But I don't see how
these are duplicates.

615
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,360
That's not how Zygons work.

616
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:38,360
They don't grow duplicates.

617
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:43,360
They kidnap the original,
so these...

618
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:51,120
These are the humans.

619
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:53,520
Retreat.

620
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:58,720
Retreat! This is a trap!
This is an ambush! (GASPS)

621
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:04,240
(SHUDDERING)

622
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:06,120
JAC: No!

623
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:10,200
Oh, no, Miss Oswald, please.

624
00:40:10,280 --> 00:40:11,440
-Please.
-Kill the traitors.

625
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,360
(JAC SCREAMING)

626
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:16,040
(ALL SCREAMING)

627
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:19,760
(SANDEEP SCREAMING)

628
00:40:20,840 --> 00:40:21,880
Is he... Is he okay?

629
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:31,400
Hello, Clara.

630
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:33,160
My name is Bonnie.

631
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,480
We want the truth

632
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:03,880
of who we are
to be acknowledged.

633
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:07,920
We want to live as ourselves,

634
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,240
at any cost.

635
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:11,880
We want a home.

636
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:13,440
DOCTOR: Well, you can't
have the United Kingdom.

637
00:41:13,720 --> 00:41:15,200
There's already people living there.

638
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:16,840
They'll think you're
gonna pinch their benefits.

639
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:20,400
We're already there, Doctor.

640
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:23,640
The invasion has
already taken place,

641
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:26,800
bit by bit over the last year.

642
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:30,840
We've won the first battle.

643
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:35,040
And now, we are
going to begin the war.

644
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:40,160
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

645
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:50,280
There's hundreds more.

646
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:52,840
They killed everybody.

647
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:54,640
We have to find out
what forms they took,

648
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:56,000
how many of them there were.

649
00:41:57,480 --> 00:41:59,400
How did this happen?

650
00:41:59,480 --> 00:42:01,520
Somebody once caught
the briefest of glimpses

651
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:04,480
of a Zygon in its proper form.

652
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:06,520
(SIGHS) A child,

653
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:11,040
who hadn't learnt to
preserve its body print.

654
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:17,600
It had been left alone to
learn these things for itself.

655
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:21,880
And then, word went
around these primitives

656
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:25,080
that we were monsters.

657
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,160
IIWell?

658
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:29,480
There isn't any back-up,
is there?

659
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:33,520
I just had to be sure.

660
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:51,920
BONNIE: (ON PHONE)
Commander calling.

661
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:53,840
"Truth or Consequences',
what is your status?

662
00:42:57,720 --> 00:42:59,200
Repeat. Commander calling.

663
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:02,000
"Truth or Consequences',
what is your status?

664
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:06,960
Commander, UNIT neutralised
in North America.

665
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:08,840
"Truth or Consequences".

666
00:43:10,080 --> 00:43:12,400
-Copy that.
-(DISCONNECTS CALL)

667
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:38,800
Bonnie speaking.
UNIT neutralised in the UK.

668
00:43:38,880 --> 00:43:40,840
More or less.

669
00:43:57,200 --> 00:43:58,680
(LINE RINGING)

670
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:05,360
-(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)
-Answer it. Say goodbye.

671
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:07,960
This plane will never land.

672
00:44:08,040 --> 00:44:10,440
Really? Clara.

673
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:12,400
Doctor.

674
00:44:14,040 --> 00:44:15,040
Clara?

675
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:16,600
There you are.

676
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:19,240
Clara, I'm glad you're okay.
Listen.

677
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:22,280
You're breaking up.

678
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:23,520
The invasion has happened.

679
00:44:23,600 --> 00:44:25,320
You're probably
surrounded by Zygons.

680
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:27,760
Get to the Tardis.
Get yourself safe.

681
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:29,880
And apparently, my plane
is never going to land.

682
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:31,720
But let's see what we're
going to do about that.

683
00:44:32,440 --> 00:44:35,200
I'm sorry, but Clara's dead.

684
00:44:35,960 --> 00:44:37,560
Kate Stewart is dead.

685
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:40,320
The UNIT troops are all dead.

686
00:44:41,560 --> 00:44:43,920
"Truth or Consequences".

687
00:44:48,680 --> 00:44:50,160
Clara!

